#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:59
msgid "Compatibility notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:61
msgid ""
"The changed error message emitted by array comparison testing functions may "
"affect doctests. See below for detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:64
msgid ""
"Casting from double and single denormals to float16 has been corrected.  In "
"some rare cases, this may result in results being rounded up instead of "
"down, changing the last bit (ULP) of the result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:70
msgid "New Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:73
msgid "divmod operation is now supported for two ``timedelta64`` operands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:74
msgid ""
"The divmod operator now handles two ``np.timedelta64`` operands, with type "
"signature ``mm->qm``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:79
msgid "Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:82
msgid "Further improvements to ``ctypes`` support in ``np.ctypeslib``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:83
msgid ""
"A new `numpy.ctypeslib.as_ctypes_type` function has been added, which can be "
"used to converts a `dtype` into a best-guess `ctypes` type. Thanks to this "
"new function, `numpy.ctypeslib.as_ctypes` now supports a much wider range of "
"array types, including structures, booleans, and integers of non-native "
"endianness."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:90
msgid "Array comparison assertions include maximum differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:91
msgid ""
"Error messages from array comparison tests such as `np.testing."
"assert_allclose` now include \"max absolute difference\" and \"max relative "
"difference,\" in addition to the previous \"mismatch\" percentage. This "
"information makes it easier to update absolute and relative error tolerances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:99
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:102
msgid "``timedelta64 % 0`` behavior adjusted to return ``NaT``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.1-notes.rst:103
msgid ""
"The modulus operation with two ``np.timedelta64`` operands now returns "
"``NaT`` in the case of division by zero, rather than returning zero"
msgstr ""
